Class Property

java.lang.Object
com.example.Property
public class Property extends Object
Represents a property with various attributes such as object ID, parcel details, geometry, owner information, and location details (freguesia, municipio, ilha).

    • Property

      public Property(String objectId, String parId, String parNum, String shapeLength, String shapeArea, String geometry, String owner, String freguesia, String municipio, String ilha)
      Constructs a Property object with all the required attributes.
      Parameters:
      objectId - Unique identifier for the property.
      parId - Parcel ID of the property.
      parNum - Parcel number of the property.
      shapeLength - Length of the property boundary.
      shapeArea - Area of the property.
      geometry - Geometry of the property in WKT format.
      owner - Owner of the property.
      freguesia - Freguesia (parish) where the property is located.
      municipio - Municipality where the property is located.
      ilha - Island where the property is located.
